Path: README.md
...
 236	
 237	Middleware provides a way to execute code before handlers are invoked, enabling cross-cutting concerns like authentication, logging, validation, and request preprocessing.
 238	
 239	### Defining Middleware
 240	
 241	Create a middleware class that implements the `RestateMiddleware` interface:
 242	
 243	```ts
 244	import { RestateMiddleware, RestateSharedContext } from 'deepkit-restate';
 245	
 246	class AuthenticationMiddleware implements RestateMiddleware {
 247	 async execute(ctx: RestateSharedContext): Promise<void> {
 248	 // Access context properties like headers, request data, etc.
 249	 const headers = ctx.request?.headers;
 250	
 251	 // Perform authentication logic
 252	 if (!headers?.authorization) {
 253	 throw new Error('Authentication required');
 254	 }
 255	
 256	 // Middleware can modify context or perform side effects
 257	 console.log('Request authenticated');
 258	 }
 259	}
...
 306	```
 307	
 308	#### Global Middleware
 309	
 310	Apply middleware to all services and objects:
 311	
 312	```ts
 313	new RestateModule({
 314	 // ... other config
 315	}).addDefaultMiddleware(LoggingMiddleware, MetricsMiddleware);
 316	```
 317	
 318	### Middleware Execution Order
 319	
 320	Middleware executes in the following order:
 321	
 322	1. **Global middleware** (in registration order)
 323	2. **Service/Object-level middleware** (in registration order)
 324	3. **Handler-level middleware** (in registration order)
 325	4. **Handler execution**
 326	
 327	### Middleware Context
 328	
 329	The `RestateSharedContext` provides access to:
 330	
 331	- **Request information**: Headers, method name, service name
 332	- **Execution context**: Invocation ID, retry information
 333	- **Restate utilities**: Random number generation, timing functions
 334	
 335	```ts
 336	class RequestLoggingMiddleware implements RestateMiddleware {
 337	 async execute(ctx: RestateSharedContext): Promise<void> {
 338	 console.log(`Executing ${ctx.serviceName}.${ctx.handlerName}`);
 339	 console.log(`Invocation ID: ${ctx.invocationId}`);
 340	 console.log(`Headers:`, ctx.request?.headers);
 341	 }
 342	}
 343	```
 344	
 345	### Error Handling in Middleware
 346	
 347	If middleware throws an error, the handler will not execute and the error will be propagated to the caller:
 348	
 349	```ts
 350	class ValidationMiddleware implements RestateMiddleware {
 351	 async execute(ctx: RestateSharedContext): Promise<void> {
 352	 // This error will prevent handler execution
 353	 if (!this.isValidRequest(ctx)) {
 354	 throw new Error('Invalid request format');
 355	 }
 356	 }
 357	}
...
