 72	
 73	### Header Propagation
 74	
 75	The `propagateIncomingHeaders` option controls whether incoming request headers are forwarded when making service-to-service calls:
 76	
 77	```ts
 78	// Forward all incoming headers
 79	server: {
 80	 propagateIncomingHeaders: true
 81	}
 82	
 83	// Forward only specific headers
 84	server: {
 85	 propagateIncomingHeaders: ['authorization', 'x-correlation-id', 'x-tenant-id']
 86	}
 87	
 88	// No header propagation (default)
 89	server: {
 90	 // propagateIncomingHeaders not specified
 91	}
 92	```
 93	
 94	This is particularly useful for:
 95	- **Authentication**: Forwarding authorization tokens through the service call chain
 96	- **Tracing**: Propagating correlation IDs for distributed tracing
 97	- **Multi-tenancy**: Passing tenant identifiers to downstream services
 98	- **Custom context**: Forwarding application-specific headers
 99	
 100	> **Note**: When `propagateIncomingHeaders` is enabled, the incoming headers are merged with any explicitly provided headers in the service call options. Explicitly provided headers take precedence over incoming headers.
 101	
 102	---
 103	
 104	## Serialization (Serde) and Error Handling
 105	
 106	All serialization and deserialization in Deepkit Restate is handled via **BSON** by default.
